      • processActors

        public void processActors(java.util.ArrayList<Actor> dudes)
        Description copied from class: Critter
        Processes the elements of actors. New actors may be added to empty locations. Implemented to "eat" (i.e. remove) selected actors that are not rocks or critters. Override this method in subclasses to process actors in a different way.
        Postcondition: (1) The state of all actors in the grid other than this critter and the elements of actors is unchanged. (2) The location of this critter is unchanged.
        Overrides:
        processActors in class Critter
        Parameters:
        dudes - the actors to be processed
